# Project Structure Guide

This repository is a multi-module Maven project for the Listing context microservice, which processes CPP cases for hearings and emits events to downstream contexts.


## Main Modules
- [listing-command](mdc:listing-command): Command API and command handlers for listing operations
- [listing-domain](mdc:listing-domain): Domain logic, aggregates, events, and common domain code
- [listing-event](mdc:listing-event): Event listener and processor modules
- [listing-query](mdc:listing-query): Query API and view for listing data
- [listing-service](mdc:listing-service): Service orchestration and resource descriptors
- [listing-common](mdc:listing-common): Shared utilities and resources
- [listing-json](mdc:listing-json): JSON schemas and related resources
- [listing-viewstore](mdc:listing-viewstore): Viewstore and persistence logic
- [listing-event-sources](mdc:listing-event-sources): Event source configuration
- [listing-healthchecks](mdc:listing-healthchecks): Healthcheck endpoints and beans
- [listing-integration-test](mdc:listing-integration-test): Integration tests
- [listing-integration-test-persistence](mdc:listing-integration-test-persistence): Persistence integration tests
- [listing-performance-test](mdc:listing-performance-test): Performance and load tests
- [listing-selective-catchup](mdc:listing-selective-catchup): Scripts for selective catchup

## Key Files
- [pom.xml](mdc:pom.xml): Maven parent POM, defines modules and dependencies
- [README.md](mdc:README.md): Project overview and API usage examples
- [azure-pipelines.yaml](mdc:azure-pipelines.yaml): CI/CD pipeline configuration
- [listing-command-api.raml](mdc:listing-command/listing-command-api/src/raml/listing-command-api.raml): all command endpoints are defined here.
- [listing-command-handler.messaging.raml](mdc:listing-command/listing-command-handler/src/raml/listing-command-handler.messaging.raml) all command handlers are defined here.
- [listing-command-api.drl](mdc:listing-command/listing-command-api/src/main/resources/uk/gov/moj/cpp/listing/command/api/accesscontrol/listing-command-api.drl) all command endpoints authentication rules are defined here. each action name should have a match in [listing-command-api.drl](mdc:listing-command/listing-command-api/src/main/resources/uk/gov/moj/cpp/listing/command/api/accesscontrol/listing-command-api.drl)
- [subscriptions-descriptor.yaml](mdc:listing-event/listing-event-processor/src/yaml/subscriptions-descriptor.yaml) all event names and their json schemas that this context listens for private and public event processors are described here. There are 2 types of events: public and private. public events start with "public." while priivate events start with "listing." for example "public.hearing.hearing-days-cancelled" is a public event, published by hearing context, "public.progression.hearing-resulted-case-updated" is a public event, published by progression context, and  "listing.events.case-ejected-for-hearings" is a private event that has been rased by an aggregate.
- [subscriptions-descriptor.yaml](mdc:listing-event/listing-event-processor/src/yaml/subscriptions-descriptor.yaml) all event names and their json schemas that this contexts listens for  event listeners are described here. These events are private, and they're being used to update viewstore. 

## JSON Schemas

All command api JSON schemas are located in the [api schema directory](mdc:listing-command/listing-command-api/src/raml/json/schema).

All command api example requests are located in the [api example directory](mdc:listing-command/listing-command-api/src/raml/json). Each file created in this folder must have the same name with the schema file created in api schema directory and should be valid against that schema. 

Each module contains its own `pom.xml` and may have submodules for API, handler, processor, or view logic. See module directories for further details.

